The 90s was a wild decade…
This is the beginning of a 90s nostalgia but I’ve been working on. The interesting thing about comedy is, until your bit is flushed out, speaking on certain *edgy* topics can be BRUTAL. Until you’ve figured out the verbiage to get your message across quickly and accurately you run the risk of dividing the room or even offending people based on their perception of what you’re trying to say. Such is true in real life. Many times miscommunication leads to conflict. 
The beginning of this bit has been in works for months. Many times this joke has bombed bombed BOMBED and now it’s one of my favorite bits. You can check back in my posts to see it in its infancy. You’ll notice the comfort level and confidence in delivery are night and day compared to how it used to be. Hope you enjoy the bit and a little insight into how I think comedy works. ✌🏻

latestPosts.caption:
Happy 11th Birthday to an Angel amongst Dogs and Men! Wish Zeus a Happy Birthday. He’ll be chillin opening gifts and eating sweet treats all day. The best Gemini that ever lived. 

This guy has been with me since the ripe age of 6 weeks. Before Chicago. Before Comedy. Before Zako Ryan. There was Zak and Zeus. Happy Birthday my boy. We still got a lot to do! I love you big dog 🐕 🐶 🎂 🎉

What an amazing weekend at the best club in the land with some of my favorite people in the industry. @sidesplitterstampa with the best @aprilmacie and of course @napow95 

Some 💐:
Comedy is littered with janky promoters and club owners that will play your friend, take advantage of you, and use you to@fill their pockets. Not all. But some. Side Splitters is a foundational room that any and all comedians can come to to figure out the game, figure out life, learn and grow in. The Tampa scene is fresh and fun and I truly believe it all begins here, at this club. 

Shoutout to BT for being one of the most SOLID men in comedy and always holding himself and everyone around him to such high standards. He doesn’t party with the comics. He doesn’t play favorites with the comics. He doesn’t bullshit. He’s professional, he’s kind, and most importantly, he knows the game. A lot of owners and promoters can learn a thing or 2 from the way this place is run. 

So shoutout BT, Side Splitters, the staff, April Macie, Natasha Powell, Sean Guest @seanguestcomedy , @jamjamcrazy and Becky for the boat trip, and of course the Tampa audience for being so damn fun. 

We really made some good times this weekend. See yall again soon!
